Name: MP - 01      Pink Tower
FullDescription: This series of cubes develops visual discrimination of size in 3 dimensions. Exploration with this material prepares the child for mathematical concepts in the decimal system, geometry and volume. The Pink Tower consists of ten wooden cubes painted pink, increasing increments from 1 cm3 to 1000 cm3.

Name: MP - 02      Brown Stairs
FullDescription: This series of prisms demonstrates to the child the change in width (breadth), while the length remains constant. Practice with The Brown Stair indirectly prepares the child for concepts in plane geometry, area and volume. The hardwood prisms are crafted in precise progressions from 1 x 1 x 20 cm to 10 x 10 x 20 cm.

Name: MP - 03      Key Unlocking
FullDescription:
Wooden Toy Lock Activity Box will keep your little one entertained opening and closing, locking and unlocking, storing and hiding.

This Lock Box has three compartments which can be accessed from ten coloured doors.

Each hinged door has a different type of fastening device and will challenge your little ones brain and fingers

The whole box can be carried by its sturdy metal handle

This is a perfect activity toy for those fine motor skills and it is fun to hide things and find them through one of its doors.

Name: MP - 04       Sand Paper - Alphabets
FullDescription: The Sandpaper Letters allow the child to understand writing before they can hold a pencil. The child uses three of the five senses; tactile, auditory and sight to learn the sound and formation of each letter                                                                                             The set contains a wooden box with 26 Uppercase Letters and 26 Lowercase Letters.

Name: MP - 05            Number Rods
FullDescription: The Number Rods introduce the child to quantity 1-10 and their corresponding number names. Through exploration with the material, the child also develops concepts in sequence of number, combinations of 10 and basic arithmetic. The material consists of 10 wooden rods, divided into units by alternating colors of red and blue, progressing in 10 equal steps from 10 cm to 1 meter.

Name: MP - 06     Red Long Bar
FullDescription: The Red Rods develop visual discrimination of length, while height, color and width remain constant. Ten solid wooden rods increasing in length in equal units from 10 cm to 1 meter.

Name: MP - 07       Large Fraction Skittles
FullDescription: The Large Fraction Skittles show how a whole can be divided into halves, thirds and fourths.

Name: MP - 08               Knob Cylinder
FullDescription:
his is a set of four wooden cylinder blocks lacquered and handcrafted to a smooth satin finish. Each block contains ten knobbed cylinders of varying dimensions. The cylinder blocks help develop the concept of visual discrimination of size.

Block A - Increases in height and diameter
Block B - Increases in diameter while height remains constant
Block C - Increases in diameter and decreases in height.
Block D - Increases in height while diameter remains const

Name: MP - 09        Spindle Box
FullDescription: These two boxes have compartments to count and store the spindles in order to help the child make the association between the symbols 0-9 and their corresponding quantities.

Name: MP - 10      Color Tablet
FullDescription: The Color Tablets teach the primary and secondary colors, and help to improve order, independence and concentraton.                       11 pairs of the colors: red, yellow, blue, orange, green, purple, brown, pink, grey, black and white in a wooden box with lid.

Name: MP - 11         Peg Board
FullDescription: The Pegboard with Colored Pegs helps develop a user's manual dexterity and hand-eye coordination.  The Pegboard with Colored Pegs has 49 holes with enough space between each to provide plenty of space to work with. Pegs can be inserted in the Pegboard with Colored Pegs to make patterns or group of colors.

Name: MP - 12         Knobless Cylinder
FullDescription: The knobless Cylinders invite a child to experience differences in height and width, the consequence of disorder, and helps to perfect coordination, concentration, independence and problem solving skills through observation.                                                                           4 sets of 10 cylinders varying ini height and/or diameter in each set. Each set in a seperate wooden box with the lid painted the same color as the cylinders: red, green, yellow and blue.

Name: MP - 13       Dressing Frames Rack
FullDescription: The direct aim in using the Montessori Dressing Frames is to help and encourage a child to dress independently. The child is indirectly advancing in fine motor skills and hand eye coordination. Each dressing frame focuses on one aspect of the dressing and allows the child to practice each step several times in order to perfect it.

Name: MP - 14          Mathematical Box
FullDescription: This Mathematical Box provide more practice with addition, subtraction, multiplication and division for the child.

Name: MP - 15    Sound Tube
FullDescription: The Sound Cylinders help to refine a child's auditory sense.                                                                                                     2 sets of 6 sealed wooden cylinders that make a distinctive sound when shaken. The cylinders are graded from very soft to loud and eich cylinder has either a red or green top and is contained in a wooden box with a matching red or green lid.

Name: MP - 16       Sand Paper - Numbers
FullDescription: The Three Period Lesson helps a child memorize vocabulary and master new works such as numerical order, numerical writing and numerical names.

Name: MP - 17            Taste Bottles
